## Known Constraints and Non-Obvious Decisions

> Document architectural decisions, workarounds, or constraints that aren't obvious from reading the code.

- [e.g., "The user session store uses Redis with a 30-minute TTL. This was a deliberate trade-off — see ADR-003."]
- [e.g., "We do not use database transactions in the reporting module due to read-replica routing. Writes still use transactions."]
- [e.g., "The frontend uses polling for real-time updates instead of WebSockets. WebSocket support is blocked by our current CDN configuration (Cloudfront + WAF)."]

